<h2>UK universities</h2>
<p>
UK university applications involve UCAS (University and College Admissions Service) that requires applicants to submit several documents such as personal statement and predicted grades. Applicants may apply for up to 5 universities; however, applicants can only apply to either Oxford or Cambridge.</p>
<img src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/s/fammuojpibfhvug/page.jpg" alt="Img" height="200" width="200"> 
<p>
Personal statement is 4000 character summary of why an applicant wishes to study a particular course.
Admissions tests and interviews for competitive universities such as Oxbridge, Durham, Bristol, Imperial, LSE, UCL and etc. and also for competitive courses such as medicine and law may be required. Admissions tests are used by universities to examine applicants’ academic potential beyond their predicted grades from national examinations. Some of these are designed to be subject-specific while others are designed to test thinking skills in general.</p>

